```typescript
for (const [x, y] of liveCells) {
  candidates.set(key([x, y]), [x, y]);
  for (const [dx, dy] of NEIGHBOR_OFFSETS) {
    const neighbor: Cell = [x + dx, y + dy];
    candidates.set(key(neighbor), neighbor);
  }
}
```

There are two `candidates.set(key(...), ...)` calls — duplication (Rule 3). I can extract a helper or unify by using the cell + offsets in one loop, treating `[0,0]` as one of the offsets. Let me think:

Option A: Extract a `addCandidate` helper.
Option B: Include `[0,0]` in an extended offsets list. But that conflates "cell" with "neighbor offset" — hurts Rule 2 (intent).

Option A wins on clarity:

